  21 /* To generate a Unicode 3.2 CNS11643.TXT, take from
  22    http://www.unicode.org/Public/Mappings/EASTASIA/OTHER/CNS11643.TXT
  23    the planes 1+2
  24 
  25      grep -v '^#' CNS11643.TXT | grep '^0x[12]' | sed -e 's/[   ]*#.*$//'
  26 
  27    and merge with the extracted table
  28 
  29      grep '^U.*kIRG_TSource ' UNIHAN.TXT | sed -e 's,^U+\([0-9A-F][0-9A-F][0-9A-F][0-9A-F][0-9A-F]*\)   kIRG_TSource    \(.\)-\(....\)$,0x\2\3  0x\1,' | sed -e 's,^0x64627 0x2F958$,0x64267    0x2F958,' | sort
  30 
  31    using a "cat ... ... | sort | uniq" command.
  32    The following duplicate must be treated by hand:
  33        U+5344 = plane 1, 0x243F = plane 3, 0x2138
  34  */
  35 
  36 /* The following table contains no hole and is therefore compact.  Nice
  37    work compared with the chaos of other character sets (or plane 1).
  38 
  39    The table can be generated using
  40 
  41    egrep '^0x2' CNS11643.TXT |
  42    awk '{print $1, $2}' | perl tab.pl
  43 
  44    where tab.pl is:
  45 
  46    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  47    $n=0;
  48    while (<>) {
  49      local($cns, $ucs4, %rest) = split;
  50      local($u)=hex($ucs4);
  51      local($c)=hex($cns)-0x22121;
  52      printf ("\n ") if ($n % 4 eq 0);
  53      ++$n;
  54      printf (" [0x%04x] = 0x%04x,",
  55              int($c / 256) * 94 + ($c & 0xff), $u);
  56    }
  57    printf ("\n");
  58    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  59 */

7633 /* The following table contains no hole and is therefore compact.  Nice
